thm erdszelem2(setvar s0, class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3) {

  ssrab2(s0, cpw(co(nat1, cfz, c1)), wa(wiso(cres(c2, cv(s0)), clt, c3, cv(s0), cima(c2, cv(s0))), wcel(c1, cv(s0))))
  ssfi(cpw(co(nat1, cfz, c1)), c0)
  mp2an(wfo(cres(chash, c0), c0, cima(chash, c0)), wfun(chash), wss(c0, cdm(chash)))
  fores(chash, c0)
  fofi(c0, cres(chash, c0), cima(chash, c0))
  mprgbir(hs0, c0, wss(cima(chash, c0), cn), wcel(cfv(chash, cv(hs0)), cn))
  mp2an(wb(wss(cima(chash, c0), cn), wral(hs0, c0, wcel(cfv(chash, cv(hs0)), cn))), wfun(chash), wss(c0, cdm(chash)))
  ax-mp(wfun(chash), wf(chash, universe, cun(cn0, csn(cpnf))))
  ffun(chash, universe, cun(cn0, csn(cpnf)))
  sseqtr4i(c0, cdm(chash), universe)
  ssv(c0)
  fdmi(chash, universe, cun(cn0, csn(cpnf)))
  hashf()
  funimass4(hs0, chash, c0, cn)
  sylbi(wcel(cv(hs0), c0), wcel(cfv(chash, cv(hs0)), cn), w3a(wss(cv(hs0), co(nat1, cfz, c1)), wiso(cres(c2, cv(hs0)), clt, c3, cv(hs0), cima(c2, cv(hs0))), wcel(c1, cv(hs0))))
  erdszelem1(s0, cv(hs0), c0, c1, c2, c3)
  mpbird(w3a(wss(cv(hs0), co(nat1, cfz, c1)), wiso(cres(c2, cv(hs0)), clt, c3, cv(hs0), cima(c2, cv(hs0))), wcel(c1, cv(hs0))), wcel(cfv(chash, cv(hs0)), cn), wne(cv(hs0), emptycls))
  3ad2ant3(wss(cv(hs0), co(nat1, cfz, c1)), wiso(cres(c2, cv(hs0)), clt, c3, cv(hs0), cima(c2, cv(hs0))), wcel(c1, cv(hs0)), wne(cv(hs0), emptycls))
  ne0i(c1, cv(hs0))
  syl(w3a(wss(cv(hs0), co(nat1, cfz, c1)), wiso(cres(c2, cv(hs0)), clt, c3, cv(hs0), cima(c2, cv(hs0))), wcel(c1, cv(hs0))), wb(wcel(cfv(chash, cv(hs0)), cn), wne(cv(hs0), emptycls)), wcel(cv(hs0), cfn))
  sylancr(w3a(wss(cv(hs0), co(nat1, cfz, c1)), wiso(cres(c2, cv(hs0)), clt, c3, cv(hs0), cima(c2, cv(hs0))), wcel(c1, cv(hs0))), wcel(cv(hs0), cfn), wcel(co(nat1, cfz, c1), cfn), wss(cv(hs0), co(nat1, cfz, c1)))
  fzfi(nat1, c1)

  diff.hs0.c(c0)
  diff.hs0.c(cn)
  diff.cv.s(s0, hs0)

  mp2an(((# " c0)⊆ ℕ ↔ ∀(hs0 ∈ c0,(# ` hs0)∈ ℕ)), Fun(#), c0 ⊆ dom(#))
  ax-mp(Fun(#), (# : 𝕌 →(ℕ0 ⋃ { +∞ })))

  mpbird((hs0 ⊆(1[...]c1)∧((c2 |` hs0)≅ <, c3(hs0,(c2 " hs0)))∧ c1 ∈ hs0), (# ` hs0)∈ ℕ, hs0 ≠ ∅)
  3ad2ant3(hs0 ⊆(1[...]c1), ((c2 |` hs0)≅ <, c3(hs0,(c2 " hs0))), c1 ∈ hs0, hs0 ≠ ∅)

  sylancr((hs0 ⊆(1[...]c1)∧((c2 |` hs0)≅ <, c3(hs0,(c2 " hs0)))∧ c1 ∈ hs0), hs0 ∈ Fin, (1[...]c1)∈ Fin, hs0 ⊆(1[...]c1))

blocks.name: erdsze
blocks.content: The Erdős-Szekeres theorem. For any injective sequence ` F ` on the reals of length at least ` ( R - 1 ) x. ( S - 1 ) + 1 ` , there is either a subsequence of length at least ` R ` on which ` F ` is increasing (i.e. a ` < , < ` order isomorphism) or a subsequence of length at least ` S ` on which ` F ` is decreasing (i.e. a ` < , ``' < ` order isomorphism, recalling that ` ``' < ` is the "greater than" relation). This is part of Metamath 100 proof #73. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 22-Jan-2015.)

blocks.name: erdsze2
blocks.content: Generalize the statement of the Erdős-Szekeres theorem ~ erdsze to "sequences" indexed by an arbitrary subset of ` RR ` , which can be infinite. This is part of Metamath 100 proof #73. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 22-Jan-2015.)
blocks.origin:
